<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Aroma year EPS rises, declares no dividend.</title>
<headline>Aroma year EPS rises, declares no dividend.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-05-29</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year ended February 28</p>
<p>			(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr, (cts)		7.0	   vs     6.7</p>
<p>    Div (cts)		 nil	   vs     nil</p>
<p>    Attrib income	   1.13	  vs     1.08</p>
<p>    Pre-tax		   1.34	  vs     1.88</p>
<p>    Tax			 0.22	  vs     0.78</p>
<p>    Interest paid	   0.70	  vs     0.22</p>
<p>    Turnover		184.46	  vs   184.97</p>
<p>    Share of associates'  0.01 gain   vs     0.02 loss</p>
<p>Full name: Aroma Liquor Holdings Ltd</p>
<p>NOTE - Aroma said it had extended its year end to June 30 and results of the current financial period would be for 16 months.</p>
<p>The company said it planned to diversify further into food and beverages as well as related hotel and entertainment businesses.</p>
<p>The company said it was looking to its hotel division for exiting growth prospects over the next two years.</p>
<p>It expected its turnover in bulk market liquor to increase this year.</p>
<p>Aroma is 50.3 percent owned by Malaysia's Mycom Bhd</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
